choices.text: You are given $W$, a set of $N$ words that are anagrams of each other. There are no duplicate letters in any word. A set of words $S \subseteq W$ is called swap-free if there is no way to turn a word $x \in S$ into another word $y \in S$ by swapping only a single pair of (not necessarily adjacent) letters in $x$. Find the size of the largest swap-free set $S$ chosen from the given set $W$.
